### Commands

## node inspect server.js

## list(100)

## c => run the server with debugger/ continue

## exec => Check expressions or variables

## exec body

## exec counter

## r => reload the project

## sb(19) => set breakpoint at line 19

## step => enter the function

## out => exit the function/ return the way back

## exec args

## cb('server.js', 19) => remove the breakpoint

## breakpoints => You can see all the breakpoints

## repl => do a logic directly in the console

## .save session.txt => save the session

## node --inspect server.js => run the server to watch in the browser
